.TH chr2png 1 "14 Jan 2025"
.SH NAME
chr2png \- @PROJECT_DESCRIPTION@
.SH SYNOPSIS
.B chr2png
.I [options]
.PP
In general, an input, an output and at least one graphics definition must be specified. This can be done with a variety of options. Please refer to the Options section below.
.SH DESCRIPTION
chr2png is a tool for converting encoded tile based graphics into PNG images. Tile based graphics were commonly used in video game hardware from the 1980s and 1990s.
.SH OPTIONS
.SS General Options
.TP
\fB\-G\fR, \fB\-\-gfxdefs\-path\fR=\fI\,path\/\fR
Filepath to graphics encoding definitions file
.TP
\fB\-H\fR, \fB\-\-profile\fR=\fI\,id\/\fR
Hardware profile to use
.TP
\fB\-T\fR, \fB\-\-chrdef\fR=\fI\,id\/\fR
Tile encoding to use; overrides tile encoding in graphics profile (if specified)
.TP
\fB\-C\fR, \fB\-\-coldef\fR=\fI\,id\/\fR
Color encoding to use; overrides color encoding in graphics profile (if specified)
.TP
\fB\-P\fR, \fB\-\-paldef\fR=\fI\,id\/\fR
Palette encoding to use; overrides palette encoding in graphics profile (if specified)
.TP
\fB\-h\fR, \fB\-\-help\fR
Display program usage
.SS Tile Encoding Options
.TP
\fB\-\-chr\-width\fR=\fI\,width\/\fR
Tile width
.TP
\fB\-\-chr\-height\fR=\fI\,height\/\fR
Tile height
.TP
\fB\-\-chr\-bpp\fR=\fI\,bitdepth\/\fR
Tile color bits per pixel
.TP
\fB\-\-chr\-plane\-offsets\fR=\fI\,list\/\fR
Tile plane offsets (see List Options Format section)
.TP
\fB\-\-chr\-pixel\-offsets\fR=\fI\,list\/\fR
Tile pixel offsets (see List Options Format section)
.TP
\fB\-\-chr\-row\-offsets\fR=\fI\,list\/\fR
Tile row offsets (see List Options Format section)
.SS Palette Encoding Options
.TP
\fB\-\-pal\-datasize\fR=\fI\,size\/\fR
Size of the palette data (in bits)
.TP
\fB\-\-pal\-entry\-datasize\fR=\fI\,size\/\fR
Size of teh data for an entry within the palette (in bits)
.TP
\fB\-\-pal\-length\fR=\fI\,length\/\fR
Number of entries in the palette

.SS List Options Format

.SH SEE ALSO
pgn2chr(1), palview(1)
.SH BUGS
No known bugs.
